    ],
    "summary": "On January 24, 2020, a leak of propylene from a high velocity oxygen fuel (HVOF) thermal spray process resulted in an explosion at Watson Grinding and Manufacturing Co. facility in Houston, Texas. The leak was caused by a disconnected hose inside one of the facility's coating booths. The explosion fatally injured two employees and a member of the public, with two additional employees injured. The explosion damaged hundreds of nearby structures including homes and businesses.",
    "recommendations": [
      "Urge member companies that handle hazardous chemicals to share information with customers about safety issues and the need to develop and implement effective process safety management systems",
      "Inform customers about CGA P-86, Guidelines for Process Safety Management, CCPS Guidelines for Risk Based Process Safety, or equivalent approaches"
    ],
